description.narrative:
Up until March 2020, the following results have been achieved in Afghanistan:
• 118,212 children in nine (9) crises affected provinces have access to education (69,210 girls and 49,002 boys);
• 3,478 Community-Based Education (CBE) learning spaces have been established. CBE is an outreach education model for underserved areas that is part of the formal education system in Afghanistan;
• 3,620 teachers out of which 1,658 females and 1,962 males have been recruited and trained using the Teachers’ Induction Training module recently endorsed by the Ministry of Education for use by all Education in Emergency actors;
• The Education Cannot Wait facilitated Multi-Year Resilience Programme in Afghanistan has contributed to reaching 56% of children affected by emergencies in 2019. It should be noted that 20,000 more girls than boys have been enrolled.
